title: “Paper Submission” page-layout: article format: html: toc: false theme: cosmo
::: {.callout-tip title=“How this works”} This page uses Netlify Forms to process uploads from a static Quarto site. Deploy the entire site to Netlify and enable “File uploads” in the site settings. Netlify will automatically create an Uploads folder in your project repository to store the submitted files. :::
Submit your manuscript
Please complete the form below and attach your Quarto (*.qmd) or rendered HTML/PDF. You will receive a confirmation email when the upload succeeds.




Don’t fill this out if you’re human: 


&lt;label for="name" class="form-label"&gt;Name *&lt;/label&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;input id="name" name="name" type="text" class="form-control" required /&gt;


&lt;label for="email" class="form-label"&gt;Email *&lt;/label&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;input id="email" name="email" type="email" class="form-control" required /&gt;


&lt;label for="affiliation" class="form-label"&gt;Affiliation&lt;/label&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;input id="affiliation" name="affiliation" type="text" class="form-control" /&gt;


&lt;label for="file" class="form-label"&gt;Upload File *&lt;/label&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;input id="file" name="file" type="file" accept=".qmd,.html,.pdf,.docx" class="form-control" required /&gt;


&lt;label for="message" class="form-label"&gt;Message (optional)&lt;/label&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;textarea id="message" name="message" rows="4" class="form-control"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;


Submit


⸻
What happens next? • Immediate confirmation: Netlify responds with a default success page (or a custom one if you add success.html). • Email notification: You’ll get a message at the address configured in your Netlify dashboard. • Storage: The file is stored in the project’s netlify/ or uploads/ directory, depending on your setup.
Customizing • Change storage: Configure a backend (e.g., S3, Supabase) via a Netlify Function if you want to store files elsewhere. • Spam protection: Netlify adds Akismet-style filtering; the hidden bot-field is an extra honeypot. • Redirects: Add a _redirects file to route to /thanks.html after successful submission.
/submit /thanks 302!
For more advanced logic (e.g., automatically linting or rendering the Quarto document), trigger a CI workflow via Netlify Build hooks or GitHub Actions.

